9:
Would you like an explanation of the
menu?
18:
Hahaha. It seems I chose well. We
shall wipe out the competition this
White Fest.
21:
As long as those two are here, our
success is guaranteed—
26:
My apologies, but I am afraid this is
my last day working here.
29:
I was ordered to aid the "maid cafe"
starting tomorrow—it is an order I
cannot refuse.
33:
How unfortunate... Though it would
be troublesome if our regulars
followed after... Wait a moment.
36:
Alk, would you mind asking
Murakumo to do one more thing for
me?
40:
Why are you asking me? Why don't
you ask him—
43:
I'll give you one of the Commission's
cookbooks on Yamato desserts.
48: Murakumo! Can I ask you a favor?
52:
Of course. Your wish is my
command.
59:
We've been expecting you, my
princess.
62:
You have a habit of leading me on...
But tonight, that changes.
65: There is no escaping from me.
73:
He is exceeding all my original
expectations. Why don't we get a
closer look?
83:
That's the best name you could
come up with?!
87:
I only acted according to your
wishes.
90:
To carry out your command, no
sacrifice is too great.
92:
That is how I was made to be, after
all.
101:
Ah, I'm sorry... This is my fault! I got
too greedy for the cookbook!
106:
Hahaha, I see you've learned how to
tell jokes, Murakumo.
109:
The temptation is hard to resist
when it involves my partner.
112:
I am truly glad I was able to carry
out my role to its fullest. It was
interesting in its own right.
116:
If you're sure... By the way, is it really
okay for you to be paying this much
attention to us? What about the
other customers—
120:
Haha... You need not fret on that
matter. Perhaps it will be faster to
simply show you.
123:
Princess, is there something you
wish from me?
126: N-no, I'm fine! I... I was just—
129: Staring at me? Do be honest.
132: A-ah! I'm sorry, I didn't mean—
139:
Very well. I forgive you. You may
gaze upon me, and only me.
152:
You, as well, have been gazing upon
me this entire while.
155:
S-sorry, I was just curious, I... I'll just
go home now!
158:
Heel. I have not given you
permission to leave.
163:
What is there to be ashamed of?
You are my customer... or is that not
the case?
166:
Well then. From this moment forth,
you are my vassal.
169:
I will do with you as I please. Right
now, I command you to look at me.
175:
What is going on... What am I
subjecting my eyes to?
179:
Why, a proud and self-absorbed
prince, of course!
183:
This character type is PERFECT for
Palpebrans, since there's no actual
royalty here to fawn over!
187:
On top of that, being from another
world gives him the unique vibe of
being a fantasy prince!
189:
Thank you for blessing my eyes. Ah,
you can ignore me now. Consider
me nothing more than part of the
furniture here.
193:
My partner, were you watching? Did
you see how splendidly I performed?
198:
I... Wow. How can you go from hot to
cold in a snap like that?
202:
Hahahaha. It was difficult at first, but
I eventually realized the underlying
logic.
205:
If they desire me, then I shall
perform to those desires.
208:
As a blade, I am keenly aware of
what my wielders wish for, after all.
210:
I like to think of it as a duel. When
swordsmen face one another, the
pressure makes one eager to take
advantage of opportunities.
213:
I only need to offer the opportunity,
and my opponent will follow. Not
many can resist the lure—that is
when I strike.
218:
Haha, perhaps this tactic is a little
too effective.
223:
Heh, I suppose I am a magical
blade. At this rate, they will be
unable to leave.
233:
It is time to wake from this dream
and return home, my princesses.
236:
But lament not. Though we part for
tonight, it need not be for forever.
239:
Should you wish for it... Please, come
again and keep this old soul
company.
